# Default CodeQL false positives configuration for CI pipelines.
# Projects can override this by placing their own .codeql-false-positives in the project root.
#
# Format: Add SARIF partialFingerprints values (one per line) to suppress known false positives.
# Lines starting with '#' are treated as comments and ignored.
#
# To find the fingerprint for a finding, run CodeQL analysis and inspect the SARIF output:
#   jq '.runs[].results[] | {ruleId, fingerprints: .partialFingerprints}' build/reports/codeql.sarif
#
# Example:
#   abc123def456  # Suppress a specific finding by its partial fingerprint hash
